The Ultimate TV Themes Collection 1947-1990

Featuring 3033 TV Themes From 2197 TV Shows

The only such listing on the internet TV Themes are a different "ballgame" than recorded pop music. 50% of TV themes never had a recorded (78, 45 or LP) equivilent. As a result to compile TV theme audio files as presented below you must:

1) Download a TV show MP4 video 2) Separate the complete audio track from the video 3) The TV theme must then be separated from the beginning and/or end of the audio file 4) Join the beginning and ending theme (if needed) 5) Many TV Themes ran over the beginning of the actual show audio - more separation may be needed 6) If item 5 is required - you'll have to fade your theme file at the beginning or end 7) All completed files must be processed with the same "silence" at the beginning and end 8) All completed files must be be balanced for volume levels so all files in a collection are the same 9) Finally a compatable photo that matches the MP3 audio must be added

TV Themes changed significantly over the years:

From 1947 through 1955 or so TV themes were "ruled" by the show sponsor. They were often very short and the theme often included product adverising. Many of these themes have been intentially left out of the listings below. TV themes continued to be short (about 30 seconds) all through the 1960s unless there was a commercial (45 or LP) recording made of the music or song. By the 1970s many TV shows had two themes available - a one minute TV show introduction and a two or three minute commercial (45 or LP) version. TV themes really improved as TV shows moved into the 1980s. Two or three minute commercial (45 or LP) versions were released for almost all TV shows and most (on TV) themes were one, two or three minutes long.

This page has 122 (random) full-length TV theme songs (that match the graphics)

They will take about 2 hours to play (Enjoy!)
